cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GR, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper deals with problems related to Hamiltonian and longest paths in graphs, which are classic topics in discrete mathematics. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The paper discusses the properties of a special kind of rectangular grid graph, which is a common object of study in computational geometry. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes algorithms to compute the longest $(s, t)$-path of an $O$-shaped supergrid graph in linear time, which is a topic of interest in data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.GR (Graphics): The paper mentions the application of the results to computerized embroidery machines and 3D printers, which are related to graphics and visualization. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper mentions that the problems of finding Hamiltonian and longest paths in general supergrid graphs are NP-complete, which is a topic of interest in computational complexity theory.
